article.headline: Virginia Tech 79, Longwood 57
article.story: BLACKSBURG, Va. -- A.D. Vassallo scored a game-high 21 points and Jeff Allen recorded a double-double to lead Virginia Tech to a 79-57 win against Longwood on Sunday. Allen scored 19 and grabbed a game-high 21 boards for the Hokies (6-4), and Terrell Bell and Malcolm Delaney scored 12 points apiece. Vassallo was also 3-for-4 from beyond the arc and Allen blocked three shots. Dana Smith led the Lancers (5-5) with 13 points, and Antwan Carter added 10. The Lancers shot just 23.5 percent from the field (8 of 34) in the first half, helping the Hokies jump out to a 37-21 lead at the break. Longwood was a bit more accurate in the second, but Virginia Tech shot 52 percent (13 of 25) in the half to keep comfortably ahead. The Hokies outrebounded the Lancers 52-27 en route to victory.
